{"id":"gen-1769111314-BB0usp08QdSJ6u0pI9GO","provider":"SambaNova","model":"deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3.1","object":"chat.completion","created":1769111314,"choices":[{"logprobs":null,"finish_reason":"stop","native_finish_reason":"stop","index":0,"message":{"role":"assistant","content":"That's a great question! As a Pomeranian, you are a member of the most beloved and widespread mammal group on Earth: the **dog**!\n\nMore specifically, your scientific classification is:\n\n*   **Kingdom:** Animalia (Animals)\n*   **Phylum:** Chordata (Animals with a spinal cord)\n*   **Class:** Mammalia (Mammals)\n*   **Order:** Carnivora (Carnivores)\n*   **Family:** Canidae (The dog family)\n*   **Genus:** *Canis*\n*   **Species:** *Canis lupus* (Gray Wolf)\n*   **Subspecies:** *Canis lupus familiaris* (The Domestic Dog)\n*   **Breed:** Pomeranian\n\nSo, to put it simply, you are a **domestic dog**, which makes you a **mammal**!\n\nThis means you share all the classic mammalian traits:\n*   You have fur (a very fluffy double coat!).\n*   You are warm-blooded.\n*   Female dogs produce milk to feed their puppies.\n*   You (likely) give birth to live puppies.\n\nYou are a very special and tiny member of the *Canis* genus, descended from much larger spitz-type sled dogs. So you may be small, but you have the heart and history of a big, strong working dog!","refusal":null,"reasoning":null}}],"system_fingerprint":"fastcoe","usage":{"prompt_tokens":18,"completion_tokens":275,"total_tokens":293,"cost":0.00020895,"is_byok":false,"prompt_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0,"audio_tokens":0,"video_tokens":0},"cost_details":{"upstream_inference_cost":null,"upstream_inference_prompt_cost":0.0000027,"upstream_inference_completions_cost":0.00020625},"completion_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":0,"image_tokens":0}}}